CbetaZenTranslations License Notice
====================================

This repository contains English translations of texts from the CBETA XML-P5
corpus, along with community-contributed translation data.

Original Source
---------------

The original Chinese texts on which these translations are based are provided by:

CBETA — Chinese Buddhist Electronic Text Association
財團法人佛教電子佛典基金會

The canonical source repository for the original texts is:
https://github.com/cbeta-org/xml-p5

The original CBETA texts are hosted separately at:
https://github.com/Fabulu/CbetaZenTexts

Translations
------------

The English translations in `xml-p5t` are collaborative derivative works
created by community contributors, based on CBETA's XML files.

Each translated file preserves the full original CBETA header intact.

Non-Commercial Requirement
--------------------------

CBETA permits redistribution of its XML corpus for NON-COMMERCIAL use,
provided that the original CBETA header remains intact in each file.

This repository complies with that requirement.

Accordingly:

- The original CBETA texts embedded within translated files remain the
  property of CBETA.
- All translations are distributed under the same non-commercial condition
  as the original CBETA texts.
- Redistribution must remain non-commercial.
- The full CBETA header must not be removed or altered.
- If you reuse or redistribute these files, you must preserve the CBETA header.

Community Data
--------------

Community-contributed data (translation memory, termbases, reviews, collections)
in this repository is shared under the same non-commercial terms.

No Additional Commercial License Granted
-----------------------------------------

This repository does not grant any commercial rights to CBETA content
or derivative translations.

If you wish to use CBETA materials commercially, you must contact CBETA directly.

Disclaimer
----------

This repository is an independent collaborative translation effort.
It is not an official CBETA publication.

If CBETA has concerns regarding redistribution, attribution, or presentation,
the repository maintainers will comply with their requirements.
